AB The present research investigated whether physical suffering would cause
   people to feel ostracized even when they are accepted by their social
   interaction partners. Participants were instructed to place their hands
   either into a circulated cold water bath (to induce physical pain) or
   into a water bath at room temperature while they were either included or
   ostracized during an online ball tossing game-Cyberball. We found that
   physical pain led people to experience social pain, while they are
   socially accepted during a social interaction. Our findings suggest that
   people with physical suffering may need extra attention in social
