   anxiety disorder as well as healthy controls. The patient and control
   groups were subdivided into two subgroups according to the subject's
   reports about previous relational peer victimization. Immediate and
   delayed physiological (skin conductance level and heart rate) and
   affective reactions to a simulated social exclusion in a ball-toss game
   (Cyberball) were recorded.
